    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nA long time ago I have set neovim to autosave sessions on `VimLeavePre` and restore it on start (see repro below). This has been working with `:restart` since it was first implemented, so running `:restart` just restarts neovim and leave me in with same windows and buffers as before. But now that behaviour is broken.\n\nDoing `git bisect` I found out that the commit `d5516daf121aa718e79bcd423ee24c24492893c0` was the culprit. Seems like the sessions are saved (I see a new `Session.vim` created if I delete it before), but not loaded. And some keymaps seem to be broken (?), like `C-d` and `C-u` and also some custom ones.\n\nI know the suggested solution is to do `:mksession! Session.vim | restart source Session.vim`, which still works, but would prefer to don't create another custom command for it when it was working before (unless it was just by miracle that worked before and that was not intended behaviour).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nUse this config\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"VimLeavePre\", {\n\tcallback = function()\n\t\tvim.cmd(\"mksession! Session.vim\")\n\tend,\n})\n\nif vim.v.vim_did_enter and vim.uv.fs_stat('Session.vim') then\n\tvim.cmd(\"source Session.vim\")\nend\n```\n\nOpen a new buffer/window and do `:restart`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`:restart` should create and load the session as it did before.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.1-dev-2+g44d1f82fbf\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nunrelated\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 10 and wsl ubuntu\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20241007-103714-ed430415\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBuilt from source",
